FAQ's






































 






What is a Self-Directed IRA?
INVESTMENT FREEDOM with the same tax advantages of an IRA. This is the quick definition of a Self-Directed IRA. Common investments using a self-directed IRA include real estate, gold and silver, limited liability companies, mortgage notes and other precious metals.



Call With Any Question
1-888-855-9856
Affordable | Professional | Quick Setup
20,000 Clients and $3 Billion in Custody
We Can Help You Too!






Real Estate, Mortgage Notes, Precious Metals, Limited Liability Companies, Private Stock
These and a long list of other non-traditional assets become available as investment opportunities through a Self-Directed IRA. In addition, the owner of the Self-Directed IRA has full control over their choice of investments, ongoing transactions and the monitoring of their IRA account.





Self-Directed IRA Gold and Silver Investing
Gold, silver, and platinum bars and coins can be purchased through a Self-Directed IRA account. Specific criteria as to the purity and the origin of these precious metals is detailed out in the Self-Directed IRA rules, but the owner of the IRA has full control in choosing the precious metal dealer and which of these approved metals they wish to purchase.





Self-Directed IRA Real Estate Investments
Real estate investments through a Self-Directed IRA may include residential or commercial properties in the U.S. or abroad in a variety of forms. Specific restrictions apply to the purchase of real estate for personal use, along with several other personal benefit restrictions.



Self-Directed IRA Rules on Prohibited Assets & Transactions
In spite of the broad range of assets available through Self-Directed IRA investing, the IRS maintains a list of prohibited asset types and transactions which would remove the tax status of a Self-Directed IRA account. Understanding what the investing rules are and how they apply to your individual situation is critical in the area of Self-Directed IRA investing and a primary reason why many would-be investors have shied away from these opportunities in the past. Our goal at Provident Trust Group is to make Self-Directed IRA investing more accessible to the average investor.

“You get the best of both worlds in a Self-Directed IRA with Provident Trust Group; Complete control, without the headaches of trying to understand and follow the complex transaction rules of the IRS all on your own.”

Why Open a Self Directed IRA with Provident?

Client Focused
Provident is owned and operated by a team of tax attorneys and highly qualified professionals. We do not sell proprietary products and are not affiliated with any bank or financial institution. What we have to offer is personalized, timely service that assists our clients in reaching their financial goals.
Complex Transactions Simplified
The Provident approach focuses on delivering clear and concise information to our clients so that they can make well-informed decisions regarding their investments. We handle all the administrative details to assure them that every reporting detail is covered and completed on time.
All it takes is a phone call, to begin your relationship with the professionals at Provident, though we’d be happy to meet you in person at our Las Vegas office as well.
Give us a call at 888-855-9856. We’d be happy to answer your questions related to retirement savings and investments through a Self-Directed SEP IRA or any other retirement plan options that you are considering.











